## Usage Examples
While this document does not contain executable code, it serves as a guideline for developers to assess and improve security practices in their implementations. Developers should refer to this document when making changes to authentication, authorization, or data handling processes.

## Best Practices
- Regularly review and update security measures as new vulnerabilities are discovered.
- Ensure that all authentication methods are implemented with the latest security standards.
- Conduct periodic security audits and penetration testing to identify weaknesses.
- Maintain clear documentation of security practices and incident responses to facilitate compliance and training.